I need to identify the financing costs incurred by the enterprise to raise funds needed for production and operation.

In an income statement, financing costs typically appear as "Financial Expenses" or similar items. These represent the costs associated with raising capital, such as interest on loans, bond issuance costs, and other financing-related expenses.

Looking at the income statement provided, I can see the line item "Financial Expenses" with a value of 4319.52 on 2024-02-01. This represents the financing costs incurred by the enterprise.
